Date:    Thu, 20 Sep 90 10:37:57 +0000
From:    frisk@rhi.hi.is (Fridrik Skulason)
Subject: Frodo's Day (PC)

As has previously been reported, the 'Frodo' (alias 4096, 4K, IDF)
virus will activate on September 22nd.

The virus will then overwrite the boot sector code with a short
program, whose function is to display the text 'FRODO LIVES' in large
letters in the middle of the screen.  It will then place a moving
border around the text and disable the keyboard - making Ctrl-Alt-Del
ineffective.

However - all the copies I have seen of this virus are defective - it
seems that the virus may even (by mistake) have garbled itself.  The
reason for this is not known, however.

The code which was garbled is the boot-writing part mentioned above.
Programs infected with the virus will therefore probably not work as
intended, but may instead hang the machine if they are run on Sept 22.

There is no great cause for alarm - the virus is fairly harmless, at
least compared to some of the real 'nasties' - but it has spread
rapidly recently....

If anyone discovers an uncorrupted copy of the virus, which activates
as described above, I would appreciate a report.

- -frisk
