Subject: Application-specific viruses (PC)

woody@chinacat.Unicom.COM (Woody Baker @ Eagle Signal) writes:
>Secondarily, it seems to me that there is a class of viruses that we
>fortunatly have not seen yet.  Application specific viruses.

Well, we have seen a few - here is a partial list.

Macho/Syslock - looks for "Microsoft" and changes it to "Macrosoft"/"Machosoft"
The (reported only) "SYS" variant of "Den Zuk".
Flip - seems to target an unknown program, perhaps an anti-virus progra,
dBase - corrupts dBase files.
There have been unconfirmed reports of two viruses - "Novell" and "123",
targeted against those products.

There may be a few more - I just don't remember them right now...

